      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "The weather will be sunny. <br/> The fresh snow and in particular the sometimes deep wind slabs are lying on the unfavourable surface of an old snowpack. Faceted weak layers exist in the bottom section of the snowpack in particular on shady slopes. <br/> Sunshine and high temperatures will give rise from the middle of the day to increasing moistening of the snowpack especially on steep sunny slopes. <br/> <br/> There is more snow than usual. At intermediate altitudes there are 150 to 220 cm of snow, and even more in some localities."
